cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of the received signal on the channel estimation and achievable rates, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with in-band full-duplex radio transceivers, which are used in wireless networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the effect of the calibration period on the self-interference channel estimation, which is a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper uses full waveform simulations to validate the obtained results, which is a multimedia technique. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the use of in-band full-duplex radio transceivers can have security implications, making this category a possibility.
